Gets the value of the result property.__

_This accessor method returns a reference to the live list,_not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the_returned list will be present inside the JAXB object._This is why there is not a set method for the result property.__

_For example, to add a new item, do as follows:_

_getResult().add(newItem)__
___

_Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list_{@link String }
codeText: public List<String> getResult() {_        if (result == null) {_            result = new ArrayList<String>()__        }_        return this.result__    }
